//An e-commerce analytics team needs to pick two products such that the product of their daily sales numbers is maximized (to advertise a pair promotion). The sales array can include zeroes but not negative numbers (sales can't be negative). However, weâ€™ll also include a variant where negatives are allowed.
Given an array arr[] of non-negative integers, find the maximum product obtainable by multiplying two distinct elements from the array. Return the product as a 64-bit integer. If the array length is less than 2, return 0.
*Test Case 01 :*
Input: arr = [0, 0, 5]
Output: 0
*Test Case 02 :*
Input: arr = [7]
Output: 0
*Test Case 03 :*
Input: arr = [-10, -20, 5, 2]
Output: 200

import java.util.*;

public class MaximumProductOfTwo {
    public static void main(String[] args) {

        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

        // Input size
        int n = sc.nextInt();

        // If less than 2 elements
        if (n < 2) {
            System.out.println(0);
            return;
        }

        long[] arr = new long[n];

        // Input elements
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            arr[i] = sc.nextLong();
        }

        // Sort the array
        Arrays.sort(arr);

        // Case 1: product of two largest numbers
        long product1 = arr[n - 1] * arr[n - 2];

        // Case 2: product of two smallest numbers
        long product2 = arr[0] * arr[1];

        // Maximum product
        long result = Math.max(product1, product2);

        System.out.println(result);

        sc.close();
    }
}
